    <!-- About the system -->
    <h3><i>About the CMCS System</i></h3>
    <p>
        The Contract Monthly Claim System (CMCS) is a practical web-based application developed to reflect real-world
        administrative workflows in academic institutions. It automates the complex process of monthly claim submissions,
        document uploads, and multi-level approvals involving lecturers, Programme Coordinators, and Academic Managers.
    </p>
    <p>
        Built using C# and .NET Core MVC, this system demonstrates modern software development practices while offering
        a glimpse into professional environments where accuracy, accountability, and usability are key.
    </p>

    <br />

    <!-- What We Do -->
    <h3><i>What We Do</i></h3>
    <p>
        CMCS enables lecturers to submit monthly claims with ease. It allows secure uploading of supporting documents,
        provides Programme Coordinators with tools to verify and approve claims, and empowers Academic Managers to oversee
        final approvals and ensure compliance. The system offers transparent tracking of claim status from submission to
        settlement and ensures consistent and reliable information across all user roles.
    </p>

